Former Manchester United forward, Dimitar Berbatov has predicted this weekend’s Premier League actions. His predictions include Manchester United’s meeting with Leeds at Elland Road on Sunday. The former Bayern Munich striker also predicted Liverpool clash against Newcastle and a crunch top-four clash as West Ham host Chelsea. For the Liverpool game against Newcastle the Bulgarian noted that the game is a big one not only for Reds in the race for the top four but also for Newcastle who need the points. He predicted 3-1 in favour of the hosts. Other predictions include: West Ham 2-2 Chelsea. Sheffield United 1-2 Brighton Wolves 1-1 Burnley Leeds 1 -3 Man Utd Aston Villa 2-1 West Brom Leicester 3-0 Crystal Palace